a. Scenario-1: LED must be ON when the button is not pressed and should be
OFF when the button is pressed.
b. Scenario-2: LED must be ON when the button is pressed and stay ON for 3
seconds even when the button is released, after that the LED should be
OFF.
c. Scenario-3: Press the button to turn ON the LED and press it again to turn
OFF the LED (toggle).

Add one more button connected to Pin 3, use Pull Up or Pull
Down resistor if necessary. And remember to initialize it in your
code. We call this as Button2 and the previous one as Button1.
 Add one external LED on the breadboard
 Create a code that will do the following:
 Scenario-4: When Button1 is pressed, all LED will be ON and it should stay ON when
Button1 is released. When Button2 is pressed and released, all LED should be OFF.
 Scenario-5: When Button1 is pressed, Internal LED will be ON, ext LED will be OFF, it
should stay that way even after Button1 is released. When Button 2 is pressed, ext LED
will be ON and int LED will be OFF, it should stay that way even after Button1 is
released.